001-d11a-4647-bd0e-434815694a68'),
(9, '8cd05e8d-e7f6-46c8-8e05-073e1f1c4c9a', 'IBPS Clerk Syllabus and Exam Pattern 2021: Topic Wise Syllabus For Prelims + Mains Exam', 'ibps-clerk-syllabus-and-exam-pattern-2021-topic-wise-syllabus-for-prelims-mains-exam', '2021-07-15', '10:14', '1626337019.png', 'IBPS Clerk Syllabus and Exam Pattern 2021: Topic Wise Syllabus For Prelims + Mains Exam', '<h2><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://localhost:8080/blog-cms-admin/article-dashboard/PHP/uploads/IBPS-Clerk-Syllabus-min.png\" style=\"height:189px; width:300px\" /></h2>\n\n<h2><span style=\"color:#f39c12\">IBPS Clerk Syllabus and Exam Pattern 2021</span></h2>\n\n<p><strong>IBPS Clerk Syllabus 2021:&nbsp;</strong>IBPS Clerk Syllabus plays an important part in knowing the exam, a candidate is appearing for. It will help the candidates to prepare well for the upcoming&nbsp;<strong>Examination.</strong>&nbsp;To do well in the IBPS Clerk 2021 Exam, it is necessary to remain acquainted with the Latest IBPS Clerk Syllabus. We have given below the latest IBPS Clerk Syllabus and Exam Pattern 2021 in a detailed manner so that the candidates can plan their preparation accordingly.</p>\n\n<h2><span style=\"color:#f39c12\">IBPS Clerk Syllabus 2021: Overview</span></h2>\n\n<table style=\"width:793px\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Exam Conducting Body</td>\n			<td>Institute of Banking Personnel Selection (IBPS)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Name of Exam</td>\n			<td>IBPS Clerk 2021</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Post</td>\n			<td>Clerk</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Selection Process</td>\n			<td>\n			<ol>\n				<li>Prelims</li>\n				<li>Mains</li>\n			</ol>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Marks Segregation for<br />\n			IBPS Clerk Exam</td>\n			<td>\n			<ol>\n				<li>Prelims: 100 Marks</li>\n				<li>Mains: 200 Marks</li>\n			</ol>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Duration of Exam</td>\n			<td>\n			<ol>\n				<li>IBPS Clerk Prelims: 1 Hour</li>\n				<li>IBPS Clerk Mains: 2 Hour 40 Minutes</li>\n			</ol>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Marking scheme</td>\n			<td>1 mark each for every correct answer in Online Test</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Negative marking</td>\n			<td>1/4th of the marks assigned to the question in MCQs</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Mode of Examination</td>\n			<td>Online</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Language of examination</td>\n			<td>English&nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;Hindi<br />\n			English Language paper has to be attempted in English only.</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2><span style=\"color:#f39c12\">IBPS Clerk Syllabus 2021 and Exam Pattern</span></h2>\n\n<p>IBPS Clerk exam is no different from any other bank exams. While IBPS issues only the broad subjects, they can be further sub-divided into individual topics, based on the questions that have appeared in the exams over the past few years. The IBPS Clerk syllabus has two papers.&nbsp;<strong>There is no interview for the IBPS Clerk Exam.</strong><br />\n<strong>(i) IBPS Clerk Preliminary Exam Syllabus:</strong>&nbsp;IBPS Clerk Preliminary Exam Syllabus comprises of three sections broadly: Reasoning, Quantitative Aptitude, and English Language.</p>\n\n<p><strong>(ii) IBPS Clerk Mains Exam Syllabus:</strong>&nbsp;IBPS Clerk Mains Exam Syllabus comprises of four Sections broadly: Reasoning, Quantitative Aptitude, English Language, and an&nbsp;<strong>additional</strong>&nbsp;<strong>section</strong>&nbsp;of Computer Knowledge and General Awareness.<br />\nThere will be a negative marking of 0.25 for every incorrect answer in IBPS Exam 2021.</p>\n\n<h4>&nbsp;</h4>\n\n<h2><span style=\"color:#f39c12\">IBPS Clerk 2021 Exam Pattern For Prelims</span></h2>\n\n<p>The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.careerpower.in/ibps-clerk-syllabus-exam-pattern.html\">IBPS Prelims Exam</a>&nbsp;is of 100 marks of 1-hour duration with 20 minutes for each section.</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>The Prelims Stage of IBPS PO will have three sections of a total duration of 1 Hour.</li>\n	<li>There will be a total of 100 Multiple Choice Questions (MCQs).</li>\n	<li>Candidates will have to qualify in each of the three tests by securing minimum cut-off marks individually for each section to be decided by IBPS.</li>\n	<li>An adequate number of candidates in each category as decided by IBPS depending upon requirements will be shortlisted for Online Main Examination.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<table style=\"width:789px\">\n	<thead>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Sections</td>\n			<td>No. of Questions</td>\n			<td>Maximum Marks</td>\n			<td>Duration (in minutes)</td>\n		</tr>\n	</thead>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>English Language</td>\n			<td>30</td>\n			<td>30</td>\n			<td>20</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Numerical Ability</td>\n			<td>35</td>\n			<td>35</td>\n			<td>20</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Reasoning Ability</td>\n			<td>35</td>\n			<td>35</td>\n			<td>20</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td><strong>Total</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>100</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>100</strong></td>\n			<td>60</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2><span style=\"color:#f39c12\">IBPS Clerk 2021 Exam Pattern For Mains</span></h2>\n\n<p>The IBPS Clerk Mains Exam has 190 questions that need to be completed in a time frame of&nbsp;160 minutes.</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>The IBPS Clerk Mains Exam will have a total of 190 questions with a duration of 160 Minutes.</li>\n	<li>There will be four sections in the IBPS Clerk Exam for Mains with different sectional timings.</li>\n	<li>Earlier, the&nbsp;<strong>Computer Aptitude and Reasoning Ability</strong>&nbsp;Section used to be conducted separately. But, as per the recent update by IBPS, both these sections have been amalgamated together constituting a total of 50 Marks.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<table style=\"width:862px\">\n	<thead>\n		<tr>\n			<td><strong>Sections</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>No. of Questions</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Maximum Marks</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Duration (in minutes)</strong></td>\n		</tr>\n	</thead>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Reasoning Ability &amp; Computer Aptitude</td>\n			<td>50</td>\n			<td>60</td>\n			<td>45</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>English Language</td>\n			<td>40</td>\n			<td>40</td>\n			<td>35</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Quantitative Aptitude</td>\n			<td>50</td>\n			<td>50</td>\n			<td>45</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>General/ Financial Awareness</td>\n			<td>50</td>\n			<td>50</td>\n			<td>35</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td><strong>Total</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>190</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>200</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>160</strong></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2><span style=\"color:#f39c12\">IBPS Clerk Syllabus 2021 for Prelims Exam</span></h2>\n\n<p>The IBPS Clerk Prelims Exam broadly has three sections namely, Reasoning Ability, English Language and Quantitative Aptitude. The Latest Syllabus for IBPS Clerk Prelims Exam has been detailed below:</p>\n\n<p><strong>Reasoning Ability</strong></p>\n\n<p>Seating Arrangements, Puzzles, Inequalities, Syllogism, Input-Output, Data Sufficiency, Blood Relations, Order and Ranking, Alphanumeric Series, Distance and Direction, Verbal Reasoning</p>\n\n<p><strong>English Language</strong></p>\n\n<p>Cloze Test, Reading Comprehension, Spotting Errors, Sentence Improvement, Sentence Correction, Para Jumbles, Fill in the Blanks, Para/Sentence Completion</p>\n\n<p><strong>Quantitative Aptitude</strong></p>\n\n<p>Number Series, Data Interpretation, Simplification/ Approximation, Quadratic Equation, Data Sufficiency, Mensuration, Average, Profit and Loss, Ratio and Proportion, Work, Time, and Energy, Time and Distance, Probability, Relations, Simple and Compound Interest, Permutation and Combination</p>\n\n<p>Apart from these common subjects asked for all the posts, candidates are required to have Professional Knowledge as well, which can be tested in the mains part of the exam.</p>\n', 'blogs', 'true', '::1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36', 'IBPS Clerk Syllabus and Exam Pattern 2021: Topic Wise Syllabus For Prelims + Mains Exam', 'published', 'IBPS,CLERK,SYLLABUS', 'public', 'IBPS Clerk Syllabus and Exam Pattern 2021: Topic Wise Syllabus For Prelims + Mains Exam', 'http://localhost:8080/blog-cms-admin/read/IBPS-Clerk-Exam/IBPS-Clerk-Syllabus/ibps-clerk-syllabus-and-exam-pattern-2021-topic-wise-syllabus-for-prelims-mains-exam', 'IBPS Clerk Syllabus and Exam Pattern 2021: Topic Wise Syllabus For Prelims + Mains Exam', 'http://localhost:8080/blog-cms-admin/assets/images/uploads/1626337019.png', 'Thu, 15 Jul 2021 13:46:58 +0530', 'Thu, 15 Jul 2021 13:46:58 +0530', '9514003d-8529-4176-9b69-a3f8b6bff1bf'),
(10, '167ab659-589c-4ee7-91c2-317f51421c4a', 'IBPS Clerk Previous Year Question Paper: Practice With Question Paper PDFs with Solution', 'ibps-clerk-previous-year-question-paper-practice-with-question-paper-pdfs-with-solution', '2021-07-15', '10:17', '1626337177.png', 'IBPS Clerk Previous Year Question Paper: Practice With Question Paper PDFs with Solution', '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://localhost:8080/blog-cms-admin/article-dashboard/PHP/uploads/IBPS-Clerk-previous-year-question-paper-min.png\" style=\"height:315px; width:500px\" /></p>\n\n<h2><span style=\"color:#e74c3c\">BPS Clerk Previous Year Question Paper</span></h2>\n\n<p><strong>IBPS Clerk Previous Year Question Paper</strong>: Every year Institute of Banking and Personnel Selection conducts exams to recruit candidates for Clerical posts in esteemed banks. The candidates who are dreaming to crack the upcoming IBPS Clerk 2021 and wondering how the exam pattern would be or confused in preparing a strategy, to begin with, their preparation, then previous year question papers is the only way to be familiar with the IBPS Clerk exam pattern.&nbsp;<strong>The official notification is expected to be released in July 2021, and the exams will be held tentaively in August &amp; September.</strong>&nbsp;So the interested candidates are advised to utilise this time and practice with the previous year question papers to crack the banking exam.</p>\n\n<h2><span style=\"color:#e74c3c\">IBPS Clerk Previous Year Question Paper with Solution PDF</span></h2>\n\n<p>IBPS select eligible candidates for Clerical Cadre posts through the Prelims &amp; Mains exam and the candidate have to qualify both stages with minimum cut off marks which are decided by the exam authority. Besides speed and accuracy, a candidate also needs proper time management and solving previous year question papers would be the best way. We have provided question papers of previously conducted&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://www.adda247.com/jobs/ibps-clerk\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">IBPS Clerk</a></strong>&nbsp;exams, hoping these would be of great help for your exam preparation. Download the previous year question papers from the article below and start practising to know the difficulty of the exam and your weak areas.</p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"color:#e74c3c\">IBPS Clerk Memory Based Papers 2020</span></h3>\n\n<p>The candidates interested in the upcoming IBPS Clerk 2021, then go through the previous year pdfs provided here and practise with these. Download IBPS Clerk 2020 memory based papers from the below table.</p>\n\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td><strong>Exam</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Questions PDF</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Solutions PDF</strong></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>IBPS Clerk 2020 Memory Based Paper</td>\n			<td><a href=\"https://wpassets.adda247.com/wp-content/uploads/multisite/2020/12/06052358/Formatted-IBPS-Clerk-Prelims-2020-Memory-Based-Mock-Paper-Based-on-5th-December-Questions--1.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Click to Download</strong></a></td>\n			<td><a href=\"https://wpassets.adda247.com/wp-content/uploads/multisite/2020/12/06041218/Formatted-IBPS-Clerk-Prelims-2020-Memory-Based-Mock-Paper-Based-on-5th-December-Solutions-.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Click to Download</strong></a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>IBPS Clerk 2020 Memory Based Paper (Hindi)</td>\n			<td colspan=\"2\"><a href=\"https://wpassets.adda247.com/wp-content/uploads/multisite/2020/12/06041242/Formatted-IBPS-Clerk-Prelims-2020-Memory-Based-Mock-Paper-Based-on-5th-December-Questions-Hindi-.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Click to Download</strong></a></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h3>IBPS Clerk Memory Based Papers 2019</h3>\n\n<p>The memory-based paper for IBPS Clerk 2019 Prelims &amp; Mains has been provided below along with its solutions. The candidate can download and start solving for better performance in the upcoming bank exam.</p>\n\n<table style=\"width:766px\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td><strong>Exam Name</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Questions with Solution PDFs</strong></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>IBPS Clerk Prelims 2019</td>\n			<td><a href=\"https://www.adda247.com/jobs/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24110246/IBPS_Clerk_Prelims_2019_Memory_Based_Paper_For_Practice.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Click to Download</strong></a></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>IBPS Clerk Mains 2019</td>\n			<td><strong><a href=\"https://www.adda247.com/jobs/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24110242/IBPS_Clerk_Mains_2019_Memory_Based_Papers_For_Pratices.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Click to Download</a></strong></td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h3>I<span style=\"color:#e74c3c\">BPS Clerk Memory Based Prelims 2018</span></h3>\n\n<p>Download the subject-wise memory-based papers for IBPS Clerk 2018 (Prelims) along with their solutions from the direct link below</p>\n', 'blogs', 'true', '::1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36', 'IBPS Clerk Previous Year Question Paper: Practice With Question Paper PDFs with Solution', 'published', 'ibps,cLERK,QUESTION PAPER', 'public', 'IBPS Clerk Previous Year Question Paper: Practice With Question Paper PDFs with Solution', 'http://localhost:8080/blog-cms-admin/read/IBPS-Clerk-Exam/IBPS-Clerk-Question-Paper/ibps-clerk-previous-year-question-paper-practice-with-question-paper-pdfs-with-solution', 'IBPS Clerk Previous Year Question Paper: Practice With Question Paper PDFs with Solution', 'http://localhost:8080/blog-cms-admin/assets/images/uploads/1626337177.png', 'Thu, 15 Jul 2021 13:49:36 +0530', 'Thu, 15 Jul 2021 13:49:36 +0530', '9514003d-8529-4176-9b69-a3f8b6bff1bf');
