CL Recruitment 2021: Eligibility Criteria</h2>\n\n<p>The interested candidates who fulfil the below-mentioned eligibility can apply for the PSPCL Recruitment 2021. Check academic requirements and age limits for various technical and non-technical posts.</p>\n\n<h3>Education Qualification</h3>\n\n<table style=\"width:945px\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td><strong>SNo</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Post Name</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Academic Qualification</strong></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>1</td>\n			<td>Clerk</td>\n			<td>Applicants must have graduation (in any stream) with a computer knowledge course certificate of 120 Hours duration</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>2</td>\n			<td>Junior Engineer or Electrical Post</td>\n			<td>The candidates must have an educational qualification in regular 3 or 4 years of diploma in electrical/ electrical and electronics/ Computer science/ IT Engineering with a minimum of 60% marks.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>3</td>\n			<td>Revenue Accountant</td>\n			<td>A regular degree in B.Com with 60% aggregate marks or a regular degree in M.Com with 50% aggregate marks or CA Inter/ ICWAI Inter</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>4</td>\n			<td>Assistant Lineman</td>\n			<td>The candidates must have Bachelors&rsquo;s degree ( in any subject) with computer &amp; shorthand knowledge.</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>5</td>\n			<td>Assistant Sub Station Attendant</td>\n			<td>The candidates should have done a full-time course in ITI/Electrical/Electrician/Wireman with minimum of 60% marks and 2 years apprenticeship experience in PSEB or full-time regular diploma in Electrical Engineering/ Electronics &amp; Communication/ Instrumentation &amp; Process Control with 60% marks</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h5><em>Note: The candidate must have passed Punjabi at Matriculation or its equivalent level</em></h5>\n\n<h3>Age Limit (as on 01/01/2021)</h3>\n\n<p>A candidate must have a minimum age limit of&nbsp;<strong>18 years&nbsp;</strong>and a maximum of&nbsp;<strong>37 years.&nbsp;</strong>Age relaxation will be followed as per the Govt. of Punjab instructions.</p>\n\n<h2>How to Apply For PSPCL Assistant Lineman Recruitment 2021</h2>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Visit the official website of PSPCL @<strong>pspcl.in&nbsp;</strong>or directly apply from the below link which is active now</li>\n	<li>Scroll down and click on the &ldquo;Recruitment&rdquo; icon on the homepage</li>\n	<li>Click on the notification for PSPCL Assistant Lineman, Clerk, And other posts Recruitment 2021.</li>\n	<li>Click on the apply button and start filling in all the required details for the post eligible for.</li>\n	<li>Upload the document and pay the application fee if applicable.</li>\n	<li>Submit the application form and download it for future reference.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h3>Application Fees</h3>\n\n<p>The candidates have to pay the non-refundable application fee while applying for PSPCL various posts. Check the application fee from the below table.</p>\n\n<table style=\"width:920px\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td><strong>Category</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Application Fees</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Applicable GST @18%</strong></td>\n			<td><strong>Total Application Fee</strong></td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>All category except SC &amp; PWD</td>\n			<td>Rs. 800</td>\n			<td>Rs. 140</td>\n			<td>Rs. 944 (bank charges if applicable</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>SC &amp; PWD</td>\n			<td>Rs. 500</td>\n			<td>Rs. 90</td>\n			<td>Rs.590 (bank charges if applicable)</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>Online Application Link For PSPCL Recruitment 2021</h2>\n\n<p>The Punjab State Power Corporation Limited (PSPCL) has begun the online registration for 2632 Technical and Non-Technical posts on its official website from 11th June 2021 onwards&nbsp;<strong>The last date to apply online has been again extended to 28th July 2021.</strong>&nbsp;The candidates are advised to apply from the below link much before the last date arrives.</p>\n\n<h4>Link to 